Program: Start the Week
Title: Cross-dressing and masculinity with Grayson Perry
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b078xf12
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 2 May 2016
On Start the Week Grayson Perry discusses the concept of masculinity in modern Britain with Mary Ann Sieghart. The new artistic director at the Globe Theatre, Emma Rice, explains how she is playing with gender in Shakespeare's Midsummer Night's Dream, and the celebrated mezzo-soprano Alice Coote talks of her career in 'breeches', singing the male role. The former artists' model, Kelley Swain reveals what it's like being the object of a work of art. Producer: Katy Hickman. Show less